---
/**
 * context-engineering/0003 · Figure 2 — "Cursor pre-indexed vs Claude Code
 * read-on-demand" (the centerpiece contrast). Copied VERBATIM from the source
 * lesson (figure + svg + figcaption incl. footnote <sup>s). References the shared
 * arrowhead markers (#arw) defined once in Fig1.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 640 250"
        role="img"
        aria-label="Cursor pre-indexes embeddings at setup; Claude Code reads the live filesystem on demand at query time."
    >
        <text x="160" y="18" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12" font-weight="700" fill="#b5179e"
            >Cursor — pre-indexed</text
        >
        <text x="480" y="18" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12" font-weight="700" fill="#2f5d3a"
            >Claude Code — read-on-demand</text
        >

        <!-- LEFT: index path -->
        <rect x="56" y="32" width="208" height="34" rx="7" fill="#f6eef7" stroke="#b5179e"
        ></rect><text
            x="160"
            y="53"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="9.5"
            font-weight="700"
            fill="#111110">At setup: chunk + embed files</text
        >
        <rect x="56" y="76" width="208" height="34" rx="7" fill="#f6eef7" stroke="#b5179e"
        ></rect><text
            x="160"
            y="97"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="9.5"
            font-weight="700"
            fill="#111110">Store vectors in an index</text
        >
        <rect
            x="56"
            y="120"
            width="208"
            height="34"
            rx="7"
            fill="#f1eef2"
            stroke="#b5179e"
            stroke-width="2"></rect><text
            x="160"
            y="138"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="9.5"
            font-weight="700"
            fill="#b5179e">At query: semantic retrieval</text
        ><text x="160" y="150" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#6b675f"
            >nearest vectors &rarr; window</text
        >
        <line x1="160" y1="66" x2="160" y2="74" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
        <line x1="160" y1="110" x2="160" y2="118" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
        <rect x="56" y="172" width="100" height="60" rx="7" fill="#e9f3ec" stroke="#2f5d3a"
        ></rect><text
            x="106"
            y="189"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="9"
            font-weight="700"
            fill="#2f5d3a">+ strengths</text
        ><text x="106" y="203" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7.6" fill="#6b675f"
            >fast recall, huge</text
        ><text x="106" y="214" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7.6" fill="#6b675f"
            >repos; finds it</text
        ><text x="106" y="225" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7.6" fill="#6b675f"
            >before you name it</text
        >
        <rect x="164" y="172" width="100" height="60" rx="7" fill="#fbecec" stroke="#9a2417"
        ></rect><text
            x="214"
            y="189"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="9"
            font-weight="700"
            fill="#9a2417">&minus; costs</text
        ><text x="214" y="203" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7.6" fill="#6b675f"
            >index goes stale;</text
        ><text x="214" y="214" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7.6" fill="#6b675f"
            >misses exact IDs;</text
        ><text x="214" y="225" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7.6" fill="#6b675f"
            >upfront indexing</text
        >

        <!-- RIGHT: agentic path -->
        <rect x="376" y="32" width="208" height="34" rx="7" fill="#e9f3ec" stroke="#2f5d3a"
        ></rect><text
            x="480"
            y="53"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="9.5"
            font-weight="700"
            fill="#111110">No persistent embedding index</text
        >
        <rect x="376" y="76" width="208" height="34" rx="7" fill="#e9f3ec" stroke="#2f5d3a"
        ></rect><text
            x="480"
            y="97"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="9.5"
            font-weight="700"
            fill="#111110">Tools: grep · glob · read</text
        >
        <rect
            x="376"
            y="120"
            width="208"
            height="34"
            rx="7"
            fill="#e9f3ec"
            stroke="#2f5d3a"
            stroke-width="2"></rect><text
            x="480"
            y="138"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="9.5"
            font-weight="700"
            fill="#2f5d3a">Search live filesystem</text
        ><text x="480" y="150" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#6b675f"
            >follow imports like a human</text
        >
        <line x1="480" y1="66" x2="480" y2="74" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
        <line x1="480" y1="110" x2="480" y2="118" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
        <rect x="376" y="172" width="100" height="60" rx="7" fill="#e9f3ec" stroke="#2f5d3a"
        ></rect><text
            x="426"
            y="189"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="9"
            font-weight="700"
            fill="#2f5d3a">+ strengths</text
        ><text x="426" y="203" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7.6" fill="#6b675f"
            >always fresh;</text
        ><text x="426" y="214" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7.6" fill="#6b675f"
            >precise on exact</text
        ><text x="426" y="225" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7.6" fill="#6b675f"
            >names; transparent</text
        >
        <rect x="484" y="172" width="100" height="60" rx="7" fill="#fbecec" stroke="#9a2417"
        ></rect><text
            x="534"
            y="189"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="9"
            font-weight="700"
            fill="#9a2417">&minus; costs</text
        ><text x="534" y="203" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7.6" fill="#6b675f"
            >more tool round-</text
        ><text x="534" y="214" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7.6" fill="#6b675f"
            >trips: latency +</text
        ><text x="534" y="225" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7.6" fill="#6b675f"
            >tokens; needs good</text
        >
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        The centerpiece contrast. <b>Pre-index = precompute recall</b> (fast, but a snapshot that drifts).
        <b>Read-on-demand = compute recall live</b> (fresh and exact, but pays in round-trips). Neither
        is "better" — they trade staleness against latency.<sup><a href="#s3" id="r3">3</a></sup
        ><sup><a href="#s4" id="r4">4</a></sup>
    </figcaption>
</figure>
